cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and understanding instructions. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a model for interpreting natural language instructions in context. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the model is able to learn grounded representations of sentence meaning and pragmatic constraints on interpretation. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is a possible category as the model is applied to tasks that involve robotic agents following instructions. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also possible as the model uses structured observations of the environment to score sequences of actions.
